# Scenario code

## Typical layout

```
scenarios/NN-slug/
├── setup.sh              # sources _shared/enable-testbench.sh
├── infrastructure/       # mock-server.js (or exception infra)
├── victim-app/           # or corporate-app/, compromised-app/, …
├── malicious-packages/   # or templates/, registry/, packages/
└── detection-tools/      # optional
```

## Mock server (Node majority)

- `POST /collect` — append exfil JSON to `{ captures: [...] }` file
- `GET|DELETE /captured-data`
- After each capture: `require('../../../detection-tools/es/forward-capture').forwardCaptureIfEnabled(__dirname, captureEntry).catch(() => {})`

## TESTBENCH wiring

- Shell: `enable-testbench.sh` (via `setup.sh`)
- Node: `npm start` with `-r ../../_shared/testbench-env.js`
- Python (22): import `testbench_env.py`

## README.md / DETECT.md in this folder

- `DETECT.md` — IOCs, log lines, Sigma, YARA, EDR/SIEM, `## Mitigation` → `scas-rules` via `load-runbooks.js`
- `README.md` — `## Mitigation Playbook` + TOC
- Mitigation or runtime changes: edit `scripts/lib/mitigation-playbooks.js` first, then run sync scripts in `documentation/platform/TOOLING.md` § Documentation lifecycle
